
Security Metrics and Executive Reporting вҖ“ README
рҹ“Ң Overview

This project focuses on evaluating Security Operations Center (SOC) performance using key metrics such as MTTD (Mean Time to Detect), MTTR (Mean Time to Respond), False Positive Rate, and Dwell Time. The goal is to analyze incident response efficiency and present findings in a format suitable for both technical teams and executive stakeholders.

рҹҺҜ Objectives
Calculate SOC performance metrics
Visualize metrics using a dashboard (conceptual Elastic Security)
Analyze dwell time for incident response
Create an executive-level security report
Provide actionable recommendations
рҹ§° Tools Used
Elastic Security (simulated dashboard)
Google Sheets (metrics calculation & analysis)
Google Docs (executive reporting)
рҹ“Ҡ SOC Metrics Overview
Metric	Value	Description
MTTD	2 hours	Time taken to detect a threat
MTTR	4 hours	Time taken to respond and mitigate
False Positive Rate	Low	Incorrect alerts generated
Dwell Time	6 hours	Total time attacker remained undetected
рҹ“Ҳ Metrics Dashboard (Conceptual)

The Elastic Security dashboard was designed to visualize:

Detection time trends (MTTD)
Response efficiency (MTTR)
Alert accuracy (False Positives)
Incident lifecycle (Dwell Time)

рҹ‘ү This dashboard helps SOC teams quickly assess performance and identify bottlenecks.

рҹ”Қ Metrics Calculation
вң”пёҸ MTTD (Mean Time to Detect)
рқ‘Җрқ‘Үрқ‘Үрқҗ·=рқҗ·рқ‘’рқ‘Ўрқ‘’рқ‘җрқ‘Ўрқ‘–рқ‘ңрқ‘ӣрқ‘Үрқ‘–рқ‘ҡрқ‘’вҲ’рқҗҙрқ‘Ўрқ‘Ўрқ‘Һрқ‘җрқ‘ҳрқ‘Үрқ‘–рқ‘ҡрқ‘’
MTTD=DetectionTimeвҲ’AttackTime

Example:
Attack: 10:00 AM
Detection: 12:00 PM
рҹ‘ү MTTD = 2 hours

вң”пёҸ MTTR (Mean Time to Respond)
рқ‘Җрқ‘Үрқ‘Үрқ‘…=рқ‘…рқ‘’рқ‘ рқ‘қрқ‘ңрқ‘ӣрқ‘ рқ‘’рқ‘Үрқ‘–рқ‘ҡрқ‘’вҲ’рқҗ·рқ‘’рқ‘Ўрқ‘’рқ‘җрқ‘Ўрқ‘–рқ‘ңрқ‘ӣ рқ‘Үрқ‘–рқ‘ҡрқ‘’
MTTR=ResponseTimeвҲ’DetectionTime

Example:
Detection: 12:00 PM
Response: 4:00 PM
рҹ‘ү MTTR = 4 hours

вң”пёҸ Dwell Time
рқҗ·рқ‘Өрқ‘’рқ‘ҷрқ‘ҷ рқ‘Үрқ‘–рқ‘ҡрқ‘’= рқҗ·рқ‘’рқ‘Ўрқ‘’рқ‘җрқ‘Ўрқ‘–рқ‘ңрқ‘ӣ рқ‘Үрқ‘–рқ‘ҡрқ‘’вҲ’рқҗјрқ‘ӣрқ‘–рқ‘Ўрқ‘–рқ‘Һрқ‘ҷ рқҗ¶рқ‘ңрқ‘ҡрқ‘қрқ‘ҹрқ‘ңрқ‘ҡрқ‘–рқ‘ рқ‘’ рқ‘Үрқ‘–рқ‘ҡрқ‘’
DwellTime=DetectionTimeвҲ’InitialCompromiseTime

рҹ‘ү In this case: 6 hours

рҹ“ү Metrics Analysis (50 Words)

The analysis indicates that the Mean Time to Detect (MTTD) is 2 hours and the Mean Time to Respond (MTTR) is 4 hours, resulting in a dwell time of 6 hours. While detection capabilities are effective, response time can be improved through automation and better incident handling procedures.

рҹ“қ Executive Summary (150 Words)

The Security Operations Center (SOC) performance was evaluated using key metrics, including Mean Time to Detect (MTTD), Mean Time to Respond (MTTR), false positive rate, and dwell time. The analysis revealed an MTTD of 2 hours and an MTTR of 4 hours, indicating moderate efficiency in threat detection and response. The dwell time of 6 hours suggests that threats remain in the environment longer than desired, increasing potential risk.

Although the false positive rate is low, indicating effective alert filtering, there is room for improvement in response speed. Delays in response may lead to increased impact during security incidents. To enhance SOC performance, it is recommended to implement automated response mechanisms, improve monitoring tools, and conduct regular training for analysts.

By optimizing detection and response processes, the organization can significantly reduce risk exposure and improve overall cybersecurity resilience.
